                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "game-id": "1debc9c19f9ffadf57ee0ebf1bc785cb",
                    "text": "A mindless creature has either programmed or rudimentary mental attributes. Most, if not all, of their mental attribute modifiers are \u20135. They are immune to all mental effects.",
                    "classes": [
                        "monsters"
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "family": {
                "name": "Painted Creatures",
                "type": "monster_family",
                "sections": [
                    {
                        "name": "Painted Behavior",
                        "type": "section",
                        "text": "Painted creatures typically adopt the behaviors of whatever they resemble. This results in creatures like a painted sheep bleating worriedly and grazing, even though any grasses consumed sit inertly inside its improvised belly before eventually seeping though its body and plopping on the ground.   \n  \nIntelligent creatures animated in this way sometimes develop a limited vocabulary. However, the construct remains mindless, their utterances follow only the most simplistic logic, and their words fall short of anything that could be considered conversation. With careful instruction, such constructs can perform mundane chores.",
                        "sources": [
                            {
                                "type": "source",
                                "name": "Pathfinder #218: Titanbane",
                                "link": {
                                    "type": "link",
                                    "name": "Pathfinder #218: Titanbane pg. 86",
                                    "alt": "Pathfinder #218: Titanbane pg. 86",
                                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                                    "aonid": 274
                                },
                                "page": 86
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "name": "Painted Treasure",
                        "type": "section",
                        "text": "A painted creature\u2019s gear is part of the creature and is also made of magical paint. Such gear can\u2019t be disarmed. If the painted creature drops any gear, the item melts into a glob of paint a moment later\u2014after dealing damage, for thrown and projectile weapons. Painted gear (including ammunition) is restored to a painted creature automatically 24 hours after it\u2019s lost.  \n  \nAt the GM\u2019s discretion, a talented PC artist might rescue a painted item by immediately and successfully Repairing it, using a hard DC of the painted creature\u2019s level. This might allow PCs to recover a unique (even magical) item that existed only in the original artist\u2019s imagination.",
                        "sources": [
                            {
                                "type": "source",
                                "name": "Pathfinder #218: Titanbane",
                                "link": {
                                    "type": "link",
                                    "name": "Pathfinder #218: Titanbane pg. 86",
                                    "alt": "Pathfinder #218: Titanbane pg. 86",
                                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                                    "aonid": 274
                                },
                                "page": 86
                            }
                        ],
                        "links": [
                            {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Repairing",
                                "alt": "Repairing",
                                "game-obj": "Actions",
                                "aonid": 2384
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ],
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Pathfinder #218: Titanbane",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Pathfinder #218: Titanbane pg. 86",
                            "alt": "Pathfinder #218: Titanbane pg. 86",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 274
                        },
                        "page": 86
                    }
                ],
